\nalmost completely destroyed by the ram pressure. The amount of gas in the wake\nof the interacting system is $\\sim50$% of the total gas of the colliding\ngalaxies after 500 Myr the galaxies start to feel the ram pressure. Nearly\n$\\sim10-15%$ in mass of all newly formed stars are formed in the wake of the\ninteracting system at distances larger than 20 kpc behind the stellar discs.\n(abrigded)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Jul 2008 08:30:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
