8 Mpc)^(-1.66 +- 0.08). The small\ncorrelation length of Halpha emitters may imply the weak clustering of active\nstar-forming galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Jul 2008 10:12:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
